OL,4,Cbold claims but detail is scarce
OL,6,FThen there's the economic
OL,7,Fimplications. Social care, hospitality
OL,8,Fand other lower-paid sectors rely
OL,9,Fheavily on workers with ILR. A higher
OL,10,Fsalary bar would make it harder for
OL,11,Femployers to hold onto staff, raising
OL,12,Ffears of labour shortages. Business
OL,13,Fgroups are likely to push back
OL,14,Fstrongly against any such move, and as
OL,15,Fwe've seen before, it can be very
OL,16,Fdifficult to govern if businesses turn
OL,17,Fagainst you.
